    "bookStockDetails":"Available",
    "aboutbook":"What I read ignores most of what I see. So, I wanted to write for people who mostly see what I see. Through Too Young to Think Twice, I intend to rekindle our desires, to cherish our individuality and to eulogize our persevering young blood. Takes me back to the memories of fearless tigers we were as boys. Takes me back to the mysterious sense of faith and coming together as one in prayer. Takes me back into reimagining the countless times of self talk and the unforgettable journey of young and deep emotions. Moments of love, boyhood, family, belongingness, loss, truth, courage, struggle and growth into acceptance. The author in his witty, beautiful, and craftily worded poems, reveals heartfelt stories that would touch every young mind. There is surely something to love about a poem when it's written about you, this is a whole book of them. Great poems along side beautiful illustrations. Would highly recommend. I found my favourites in the 'He has a heart' but a lot of my favourites were also scattered in between the lines and poems in the first two parts. Beauty in words.     ",
